      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(webchat): fall back to resolved name when senderLabel is empty",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nIn WebChat UI, `sessions_send` inter-session messages render without sender attribution when `senderLabel` is empty or whitespace-only. The root cause: `group.senderLabel?.trim()` returns `\"\"` (empty string), and `??` only treats `null`/`undefined` as missing — so `\"\" ?? resolvedName` keeps the empty string.\n\n## Fix\n\nOne line in `ui/src/ui/chat/grouped-render.ts`:\n\n```diff\n- const userLabel = group.senderLabel?.trim();\n+ const userLabel = group.senderLabel?.trim() || null;\n```\n\n`|| null` converts empty/whitespace to `null`, allowing `??` to correctly fall back.\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `ui/src/ui/chat/grouped-render.ts`: +3/-1\n- `ui/src/ui/chat/grouped-render.test.ts`: +65 (2 cases: empty + whitespace senderLabel)\n\n## Related\n\nFixes #92327\n\n### Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: `senderLabel?.trim()` returning `\"\"` bypasses `??` fallback — empty-string sender labels render blank instead of showing the resolved user/assistant name.\n\n**Environment**: Linux Node 24, OpenClaw control-ui mock served at `127.0.0.1:5187`, verified in browser via Playwright.\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Start mock UI: `node --import tsx scripts/control-ui-mock-dev.ts`\n2. Open `http://127.0.0.1:5187/chat` in browser\n3. Evaluate fix in browser console (demonstrates the exact code path from `grouped-render.ts`)\n\n**Evidence — before vs after**:\n\n```\n=== BEFORE fix (broken) ===\n> ''.trim() ?? 'FallbackName'\n\"\"                         ← empty! ?? doesn't fall back for empty string\n\n> '   '.trim() ?? 'FallbackName'\n\"\"                         ← whitespace also broken\n\n=== AFTER fix (this PR) ===\n> (''.trim() || null) ?? 'FallbackName'\n\"FallbackName\"             ← correct fallback\n\n> ('   '.trim() || null) ?? 'FallbackName'\n\"FallbackName\"             ← whitespace also fixed\n\n> ('Iris'.trim() || null) ?? 'FallbackName'\n\"Iris\"                     ← valid labels preserved unchanged\n```\n\n![WebChat proof — mock UI with fix applied](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/fsdwen/openclaw/fix/92327-webchat-senderlabel-empty/92394-webchat-proof.jpg)\n\n**Observed result**: Empty/whitespace `senderLabel` now correctly falls back to the resolved name. Valid non-empty labels preserved unchanged. Unit tests confirm both user-role and assistant-role fallback paths.\n\n**Not tested**: Live gateway with multi-agent `sessions_send` (requires full OpenClaw deployment with real inter-session message payloads).\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "fix/92327-webchat-senderlabel-empty",
